summary: People tend to give BW credit for being the first actually compelling story in the main series Pokemon games and yeah BW was...
body: People tend to give BW credit for being the first actually compelling story in the main series Pokemon games and yeah BW was great but honestly… RS deserves more recognition. The character writing wasn’t totally on point yet (ORAS made a lot of strides in that department) but Hoenn as a region felt so real and diverse. I remember being a kid and just, like… hanging around Slateport. Not for gameplay reasons, but just because I liked it. I could run around on the beach and listen to the music and feel like I was in a bustling but airy port town, wind blowing through my hair as I watched ships depart from the harbor. Or standing next to that weirdly introspective kid in Petalburg City, staring into the water with him. Going to the berry master’s house and suddenly I’m a simple farmer living out in the woods, planting my Orans and Pechas and Sitruses. Hoenn is so… good
